<refentry id='rtwizard'>
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>rtwizard</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>nged</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo class='source'>BRL-CAD</refmiscinfo>
    <refmiscinfo class='manual'>BRL-CAD User Commands</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>
  <refnamediv id='name'>
    <refname>rtwizard</refname>
    <refpurpose>rtwizard is a tool for creating images of BRL-CAD geometry databases</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  
  <!-- body begins here -->
  <refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>rtwizard</command>
      <arg choice='opt'><replaceable>database.g</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1 id='description'>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>
      The <application>rtwizard</application> tool assists in the
      creation of images from BRL-CAD databases. The design philosophy
      behind the <application>rtwizard</application> is to provide
      you, the user, with a choice of several image types. Once the
      selection is made, you need only configure a minimum of options
      before a picture can be made. The user is then free to tweak
      options and generate new images.
    </para>

    <para>
      If <application>rtwizard</application> is started without
      specifying a BRL-CAD database on the command line, you are first
      presented with the database selection page. Use the file browser
      on the page to find the desired BRL-CAD database. Once you have
      selected the desired file, the wizard interface provide options
      for rendering a variety of image types of specified geometry.
    </para>
  </refsect1>
  
  <refsect1 id='hints'>
    <title>HINTS</title>
    <para>
      <application>BRL-CAD</application> database names conventionally end with
      <markup>.g</markup>.
    </para>

    <para>
      It is currently not possible to change the BRL-CAD database once
      one has been opened.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

